The sample size was estimated using GraphPad StatMat 2.00 software (Graph Pad Inc., Boston, United States). Based on the pilot study, the required sample size came up to 40 in each group which has a 90% power to detect a difference between means of 0.36 with a significance level (alpha) of 0.05 (two-tailed), effect size 0.728 and 95% confidence interval. In 90% (the power) of those experiments, the P value will be less than 0.05 (two-tailed) so the results will be deemed “statistically significant”. In the remaining 10% of the experiments, the difference between means will be deemed “not statistically significant”,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
